    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix gen_usim_data out-of-bounds access with 9-digit MSIN\n\n### Summary\nThe `gen_usim_data()` function in conf_usim.c was accessing memory out of bounds when processing 9-digit MSIN values, causing potential segfaults or incorrect IMSI generation. The same issue existed in `gen_emm_data()` in conf_emm.c.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/TOOLS/conf_usim.c`: Added bounds checking before accessing MSIN digits in IMSI construction\n- `openair3/NAS/TOOLS/conf_emm.c`: Applied same bounds checking fix for consistency\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running OAI5G with a configuration that includes 9-digit MSIN values in the SIM section, the system would crash with a segmentation fault during USIM data generation. The crash occurred when accessing `u->msin[9]` for 9-digit MSINs.\n\nUsers may observe:\n- Segmentation fault during startup when generating UE configuration\n- Incorrect IMSI values in generated .usim.nvram files\n- Inconsistent behavior between 9-digit and 10-digit MSIN configurations\n\nThe issue can be reproduced by configuring any UE with a 9-digit MSIN value in the configuration file and attempting to generate USIM data.\n"
}